  "body": "# Bug Report\r\nQuo2 component library `color picker` component has an offset half circle on the selected color.\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nHappened both in the `color picker` component as well as in every component that uses the `color picker` as part of testing (i.e. `gradient cover` component), on Android only (tested on a Xiaomi Red 5 Plus).\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n<img width=\"221\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-07-31 alle 08 57 51\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/122543089/13b809bc-de31-42e0-baa8-3de1add28ef4\">\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n![](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/122543089/256863331-a058ccb0-b5ea-44ee-be22-1f9d21bdb238.jpg)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Open Status\r\n2. Go to the Quo2.0 preview\r\n3. Go to colors > color picker component\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly \r\n- Operating System: Android\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
